Saussure, 1877
</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="04D9EFABD265F47EFF4CFD11FCA0FBD2" pageId="1" pageNumber="145" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="4C7CBC20D265F47EFF4CFD11FE20FC7E" blockId="1.[151,1437,658,1117]" pageId="1" pageNumber="145">
<emphasis id="7EB76032D265F47EFF4CFD11FEA1FD23" bold="true" box="[151,276,658,684]" pageId="1" pageNumber="145">Diagnosis:</emphasis>
This genus was described for the crickets with swollen frons and long, narrowed mandibles, previously placed in 
<taxonomicName id="8BC3C7A3D265F47EFED3FD34FD8FFD5E" authority="Saussure. The" authorityName="Saussure. The" authorityYear="1877" box="[264,570,695,721]" class="Insecta" family="Gryllidae" genus="Scapsipedus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="145" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="7EB76032D265F47EFED3FD34FE27FD5E" box="[264,402,695,721]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="145">Scapsipedus</emphasis>
Saussure. The
</taxonomicName>
name is derived from the habit of constructing an awning or hood over the entrance to their burrows as reported by 
<bibRefCitation id="2852C1D1D265F47EFDB6FD58FC80FD79" author="Alexander, R. D." box="[621,821,731,758]" pageId="1" pageNumber="145" pagination="130 - 223" refId="ref5262" refString="Alexander, R. D. (1961) Aggressiveness, territoriality and sexual behaviour in field crickets (Orthoptera: Gryllidae). Behaviour, 17, 130 - 223. https: // doi. org / 10.1163 / 156853961 X 00042" type="journal article" year="1961">Alexander (1961)</bibRefCitation>
in the 
<typeStatus id="93780282D265F47EFC51FD58FC0FFD7A" box="[906,954,731,757]" pageId="1" pageNumber="145">type</typeStatus>
species. Head dorso-ventrally elongate in most species due to lengthened mouth parts. Forewings are with two harp veins. Tympanum is on outer face only. Pronotum is usually wider at anterior end than at posterior ending. All species of 
<taxonomicName id="8BC3C7A3D265F47EFBF7FCA0FB71FCB2" authorityName="Randell, 1964:" authorityYear="1586" box="[1068,1220,803,829]" class="Insecta" family="Gryllidae" genus="Velarifictorus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="145" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="7EB76032D265F47EFBF7FCA0FB71FCB2" box="[1068,1220,803,829]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="145">Velarifictorus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are clearly characterized by similar male genitalia: the epiphallus is rather short, with a pair of hind lateral processes and unpaired median projection between them; the ectoparameres are simple, elongate and more or less curved, with the small mesal lobe connected with the ectoparamere by one rather narrow sclerotized ribbon. The endoparameres are not very long and with a large proximal apodeme; the spermatophore sac is more or less small and with almost straight proximal half of virga.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="4C7CBC20D265F47EFF1CFC79FCA0FBD2" blockId="1.[151,1437,658,1117]" pageId="1" pageNumber="145">
<emphasis id="7EB76032D265F47EFF1CFC79FEDCFB9B" bold="true" box="[199,361,1018,1044]" pageId="1" pageNumber="145">Composition:</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="8BC3C7A3D265F47EFEABFC78FDBDFB9A" authorityName="Randell, 1964:" authorityYear="1586" box="[368,520,1019,1045]" class="Insecta" family="Gryllidae" genus="Velarifictorus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="145" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="7EB76032D265F47EFEABFC78FDBDFB9A" box="[368,520,1019,1045]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="145">Velarifictorus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
belongs to the tribe 
<taxonomicName id="8BC3C7A3D265F47EFD2BFC78FBA2FB9A" authority="Laicharting, 1781" authorityName="Laicharting" authorityYear="1781" box="[752,1047,1019,1045]" class="Insecta" family="Gryllidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="145" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Gryllini">Gryllini Laicharting, 1781</taxonomicName>
and subtribe 
<taxonomicName id="8BC3C7A3D265F47EFB6BFC78FF67FBB6" authority="Laicharting, 1781" authorityName="Laicharting" authorityYear="1781" class="Insecta" family="Gryllidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="145" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subTribe" subTribe="Gryllina">Gryllina Laicharting, 1781</taxonomicName>
. The genus comprises 108 species worldwide and they are classified within three subgenera, 
<taxonomicName id="8BC3C7A3D265F47EFB39FB9CFAFAFBB7" authorityName="Otte &amp; Alexander" authorityYear="1983" box="[1250,1359,1055,1080]" class="Insecta" family="Gryllidae" genus="Buangina" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="145" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="7EB76032D265F47EFB39FB9CFAFAFBB7" box="[1250,1359,1055,1080]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="145">Buangina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="8BC3C7A3D265F47EFA87FB9CFE8CFBD2" authorityName="Gorochov" authorityYear="2001" class="Insecta" family="Gryllidae" genus="Pseudocoiblemmus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="145" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="7EB76032D265F47EFA87FB9CFE8CFBD2" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="145">Pseudocoiblemmus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="8BC3C7A3D265F47EFEADFBC0FCA4FBD2" authority="(Cigliano et al., 2022)" baseAuthorityName="Cigliano" baseAuthorityYear="2022" box="[374,785,1091,1117]" class="Insecta" family="Gryllidae" genus="Velarifictorus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="145" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="7EB76032D265F47EFEADFBC0FDBBFBD2" box="[374,526,1091,1117]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="145">Velarifictorus</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="2852C1D1D265F47EFDC6FBC0FCBFFBD2" author="Cigliano, M. M. &amp; Braun, H. &amp; Eades, D. C. &amp; Otte, D." box="[541,778,1091,1117]" pageId="1" pageNumber="145" refId="ref5451" refString="Cigliano, M. M., Braun, H., Eades, D. C. &amp; Otte, D. (2022) Orthoptera Species File online. Version 5.0 / 5.0. Available from: http: // orthoptera. SpeciesFile. org (accessed 15 February 2022)" type="url" year="2022">
Cigliano 
<emphasis id="7EB76032D265F47EFD5CFBC0FD0DFBD2" box="[647,696,1091,1117]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="145">et al</emphasis>
., 2022
</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
